        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/25878497/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/25878497/" class="">第212页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/vitanuova/" class=" " title="Adiyat">Adiyat</a>
                (Spiritual Chivalry Style)
              
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="25878497">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">但这并不意味着每一位启蒙运动哲学家都接受了孟德斯鸠关于共和国的原则是美德这一假说，因而在某种程度上都抱有一种矛盾的历史观

But it does mean that every philosophe was in some degree involved in the contradictory vision of history which arose from accepting the Montesquieuan premise that virtue was the principle of republics

显然把意思弄反了。试译：“但这的确意味着每一位启蒙运动哲学家都在某种程..</span>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/25878497/">(<span class="">2回应</span>)</a>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2013-04-19 20:24</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>但这并不意味着每一位启蒙运动哲学家都接受了孟德斯鸠关于共和国的原则是美德这一假说，因而在某种程度上都抱有一种矛盾的历史观</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>But it does mean that every philosophe was in some degree involved in the contradictory vision of history which arose from accepting the Montesquieuan premise that virtue was the principle of republics<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>显然把意思弄反了。试译：“但这的确意味着每一位启蒙运动哲学家都在某种程度上抱有一种矛盾的历史观，这是由于他们接受了孟德斯鸠关于共和国原则是美德这一假说。”<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>公民权可以分配给贵族政体或民主政体</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>The citizenry might be distributed into an aristocracy and a democracy<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>citizenry指公民集体，不是“公民权”，应为“公民们可以散居在贵族政府或民主政府中”。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>他是否对他所说的日期或地方有幻觉，是无关紧要的。</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>It does not seem to matter whether or not he had this vision on the day or at the place he claimed.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>这里说的是吉本追忆他在卡庇托神庙附近产生写罗马衰亡史念头的那段著名文字，意为：”至于他是否有在他声称的那一天或那个地方产生这个幻想，是无关紧要的。“

