                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/25874464/" class="">第211页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/vitanuova/" class=" " title="Adiyat">Adiyat</a>
                (Spiritual Chivalry Style)
              
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="25874464">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">世俗世界的哲人必须行动并思考其行动的理由，这种综合性的哲学在雅典和罗马是抱着最伟大的终极目的加工而成的。

Philosophic man in a secular universe must act and contemplate the reason for his actions, and it was in Athens and Rome that the philosophy of this combination had been worked out with the greatest finality.

with the greatest finality应该是指这种哲学已经达到十分完善的程度，而不是”抱着最...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2013-04-19 15:49</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>世俗世界的哲人必须行动并思考其行动的理由，这种综合性的哲学在雅典和罗马是抱着最伟大的终极目的加工而成的。</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Philosophic man in a secular universe must act and contemplate the reason for his actions, and it was in Athens and Rome that the philosophy of this combination had been worked out with the greatest finality.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>with the greatest finality应该是指这种哲学已经达到十分完善的程度，而不是”抱着最伟大的终极目的“。试译：”在雅典和罗马，结合了这两个方面的哲学已被创造出来并达到无可变更的极致。“<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>英法启蒙运动（包括它的美国变种）因此而受到谴责，说它继承的是文艺复兴的公民人本主义和古典共和主义的传统，它认为古代哲学的失败与古代政治的失败是分不开的。</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>In consequence, the Anglo-French Enlightenment (including its American variant) was condemned to carry on the civic humanist and classical republican tradition of the Renaissance, and to see the failure of ancient philosophy as one with the failure of ancient politics.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>和上页一样，这里的condemned不是指”受到谴责“，而是”注定……“。试译：”英法启蒙运动（包括它的美国变种）因此注定要继承文艺复兴的公民人本主义和古典共和主义的传统，注定要认为古代哲学的失败与古代政治的失败是分不开的。“<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>另外这页有些词译得不准，如flourished(盛行、大行其道)译为”形成“，flawed（被玷污、有瑕疵）译为”湮没“，magistrates（泛指官员）译为”执政官“。
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







